40 Onion Marmalade
2 Pizza Bases
1 Tomato Passata
12 Balsamic Vinegar
20 Walnuts
125 Goat's Cheese
40 Wild Rocket
1 Olive Oil for the Dressing

a) Put the tomato passata in a bowl and add a pinch of salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar. Mix.

a) Lay the pizza bases on a large baking tray (use 2 if you need to). b) Divide the tomato sauce between your pizzas. c) Spread the tomato sauce evenly over each leaving a 1cm border clear of sauce.

a) Crumble the goat's cheese into small chunks and dot evenly on top of the tomato sauce on your pizza. b) Use a teaspoon to dot small spoonfuls of onion marmalade onto the pizza base too. c) Grind over some black pepper.

a) Bake on the top shelf of your oven until both the cheese and the base are golden, 8-10 mins.

a) Meanwhile, put the balsamic vinegar in a large bowl and add the olive oil (see ingredients list for amount). b) Add a pinch of salt and pepper and mix with a fork. c) Place the rocket and walnuts on top of the dressing (we will toss together just before serving).

a) Once the pizzas are cooked, remove from your oven. b) Toss the rocket, walnuts and dressing together in the bowl. Serve the salad alongside the pizzas (or on top if you prefer!). Enjoy!